    "rich_text_CQwnLV": {
      "type": "rich-text",
      "blocks": {
        "text_n4gY8q": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p></p><h3><strong>InBuilt Electric Ovens</strong></h3><p>Our <a href=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/inbuilt-electric-ovens\">inbuilt electric ovens</a> are designed for kitchens that value a seamless and integrated look. Installed directly into cabinetry, these ovens align with modern design standards while offering ergonomic access—often at eye-level or below your cooktop.</p><p>Built with precision heating elements and fan-forced functionality, these ovens offer consistent heat distribution—ideal for baking, roasting, and grilling. Many models also include programmable timers, multi-function modes, cool-touch doors, and even pyrolytic self-cleaning cycles. If precision and consistency are key to your cooking, an inbuilt electric oven offers reliability and ease.</p><h3><strong>Freestanding Ovens</strong></h3><p><a href=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/freestanding-ovens\">Freestanding ovens</a> combine oven and cooktop into a single unit—ideal for homes without built-in cabinetry or for those wanting a standalone feature appliance. These models are available in standard 60cm sizes for compact kitchens, as well as larger 90cm options suited to growing families or entertainers.</p><p>Freestanding ovens typically include generous internal capacity, built-in grill functionality, and high-powered cooktops. With the added flexibility of installation and robust performance, they remain a favourite for households that require an all-in-one cooking solution.</p><h3><strong>Microwave Ovens</strong></h3><p><a href=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/microwave-ovens\">Microwave ovens</a> are essential for efficient, fast-paced kitchens. They provide quick reheating, defrosting, and in many cases, multi-function features such as grilling or baking. Models within our collection feature user-friendly digital interfaces, inverter technology for even heating, and sleek designs that complement any kitchen aesthetic.</p><p>Whether used daily or as a secondary appliance, a high-quality microwave oven can elevate convenience without compromising style.</p><h3><strong>Gas Cooktops</strong></h3><p>For chefs who value intuitive control, <a href=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/gas-cooktops\">gas cooktops</a> remain the gold standard. With visible flames and rapid heat response, they allow for precise temperature adjustments in real time. Our gas cooktops come equipped with safety features such as flame failure protection, as well as durable cast iron trivets and high-output wok burners for more advanced cooking needs.</p><p>Gas cooktops are available in multiple configurations—from compact two-burner models to expansive five-burner layouts—offering a versatile solution for both small and large kitchens.</p><h3><strong>Electric Cooktops</strong></h3><p><a href=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/electric-cooktops\">Electric cooktops</a> offer a smooth, flat cooking surface that is easy to clean and fits beautifully into minimalist kitchen designs. They use radiant heating beneath a glass-ceramic surface to evenly distribute heat, making them ideal for low-maintenance, everyday cooking.</p><p>These models typically include touch or dial controls, residual heat indicators, and multiple cooking zones. For households that value simplicity and sleek aesthetics, an electric cooktop is a practical and attractive option.</p><h3><strong>Induction Cooktops</strong></h3><p><a href=\"https://www.cookandbathe.com.au/collections/induction-cooktops\">Induction cooktops</a> represent the next generation of kitchen technology. These units heat pots and pans directly via electromagnetic energy, resulting in ultra-fast heating, exceptional energy efficiency, and enhanced safety. The surface remains cool to the touch, making it ideal for families or open-plan kitchens.</p><p>With advanced features such as child locks, boost functions, bridge zones, and precise power adjustment, induction cooktops offer control and convenience tailored for the modern cook.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
